issue.title: otel_for_api
issue.body:
下面给你一套Spring Boot（Java）侧的完整落地方案，覆盖：无侵入 Java Agent 推荐方案（首选）+ Spring Boot 原生 Micrometer/OTel 方案（可选），并给出K8s Deployment/Collector Sidecar YAML、环境变量、采样/传播与验证方法。按此配置，API1→API2→API3 会自动提取/注入 W3C Trace Context，Sidecar Collector 统一把 Trace 经 Kafka Exporter 发到你的 Kafka。

重要提示：Kong DP 不要把 Trace 直接发到 API Pod 的 sidecar。给 Kong 配一个集中式 Collector Service或给 Kong Pod 自己加 sidecar。本文仅配置“API Pod 内的 sidecar”。

⸻

0. 命名与传播约定（适用于 API1/2/3）
	•	service.name: api1 / api2 / api3
	•	传播器：tracecontext,baggage（如需兼容旧链路再加 b3）
	•	与 Kong OTel 插件一致：header_type: w3c
	•	出口：OTLP → 本 Pod 的 otel-collector sidecar → Kafka

⸻

1) 推荐方案：Java Agent 无侵入自动埋点

1.1 Deployment（以 API1 为例，API2/3 类似改名即可）

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: api1
  namespace: your-ns
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels: { app: api1 }
  template:
    metadata:
      labels: { app: api1 }
      annotations:
        # 可选：让 k8sattributes processor 识别此服务名
        instrumentation.opentelemetry.io/service-name: "api1"
    spec:
      volumes:
        - name: otel-agent
          emptyDir: {}
        - name: otelcol-config
          configMap:
            name: api1-otelcol-config     # 见下文 ConfigMap
      initContainers:
        - name: dl-otel-javaagent
          image: curlimages/curl:8.7.1
          command: ['sh','-c']
          args:
            - >
              curl -fsSL -o /otel/opentelemetry-javaagent.jar
              https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-java-instrumentation/releases/download/v2.7.0/opentelemetry-javaagent.jar
          volumeMounts:
            - { name: otel-agent, mountPath: /otel }
      containers:
        - name: app
          image: your-registry/api1:1.0.0
          imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
          ports:
            - { name: http, containerPort: 8080 }
          env:
            # 基本资源与命名
            - { name: OTEL_SERVICE_NAME, value: "api1" }
            - { name: OTEL_RESOURCE_ATTRIBUTES, value: "service.namespace=your-ns,deployment.environment=prod" }

            # 传播器与采样（与 Kong 一致）
            - { name: OTEL_PROPAGATORS, value: "tracecontext,baggage" }
            - { name: OTEL_TRACES_SAMPLER, value: "parentbased_traceidratio" }
            - { name: OTEL_TRACES_SAMPLER_ARG, value: "1.0" }   # 联调期 100% 采样，稳定后可下调

            # 输出到本 Pod sidecar（使用 OTLP/HTTP 4318）
            - { name: OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER, value: "otlp" }
            - { name: OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_PROTOCOL, value: "http/protobuf" }
            - { name: OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT, value: "http://127.0.0.1:4318" }

            # 可选：仅启用 traces，关闭 metrics/logs 自动导出
            - { name: OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER, value: "none" }
            - { name: OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER, value: "none" }

            # 如需把入站/出站 HTTP 名称更友好（可选）
            - { name: OTEL_INSTRUMENTATION_COMMON_DEFAULT_ENABLED, value: "true" }
          volumeMounts:
            - { name: otel-agent, mountPath: /otel }
          # 最稳妥的方式：通过 JAVA_TOOL_OPTIONS 注入 agent，无需改 entrypoint
          envFrom: []
          # 直接设置 JVM 选项
          env:
            - name: JAVA_TOOL_OPTIONS
              value: "-javaagent:/otel/opentelemetry-javaagent.jar"
            # 上面已有 env，合并时请保留所有 OTEL_* 变量
          # 如你的镜像使用固定 entrypoint，也可改用 command/args 注入 -javaagent

        - name: otelcol
          image: otel/opentelemetry-collector-contrib:0.102.0
          args: ["--config=/etc/otelcol-contrib/config.yaml"]
          ports:
            - { name: otlp-http, containerPort: 4318 }
            - { name: otlp-grpc, containerPort: 4317 }
          volumeMounts:
            - { name: otelcol-config, mountPath: /etc/otelcol-contrib }

API2/3：复制本部署，替换 metadata.name、labels、OTEL_SERVICE_NAME、ConfigMap 名字等。

1.2 Sidecar Collector 配置（ConfigMap）

仅 traces → Kafka；如果你的 Kafka 是 mTLS，请在 exporters.kafka.tls/sasl 处补齐证书与认证。

apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: api1-otelcol-config
  namespace: your-ns
data:
  config.yaml: |
    receivers:
      otlp:
        protocols:
          http:
          grpc:

    processors:
      batch: {}
      # 丰富 K8s 元数据，便于在 UI 里按 Pod/Namespace/Deployment 过滤
      k8sattributes:
        extract:
          metadata:
            - k8s.namespace.name
            - k8s.pod.name
            - k8s.deployment.name
            - k8s.pod.uid
      resource:
        attributes:
          - key: service.name
            action: upsert
            from_attribute: service.name   # 由 OTEL_SERVICE_NAME 注入
          - key: service.namespace
            action: upsert
            from_attribute: service.namespace

    exporters:
      kafka:
        brokers: ["kafka-1:9092","kafka-2:9092","kafka-3:9092"]
        topic: "otcol_traces"            # 统一 traces topic
        encoding: "otlp_proto"           # 与消费端一致
        # 如需 TLS/mTLS：
        # tls:
        #   ca_file: /etc/kafka/ca.pem
        #   cert_file: /etc/kafka/tls.crt
        #   key_file: /etc/kafka/tls.key
        #   insecure_skip_verify: false
        # sasl:
        #   mechanism: SCRAM-SHA-512
        #   username: xxx
        #   password: yyy
        #   tls:
        #     insecure_skip_verify: false

    service:
      pipelines:
        traces:
          receivers: [otlp]
          processors: [k8sattributes, resource, batch]
          exporters: [kafka]

若你的 Kafka 期望 traces/metrics/logs 分不同 topic（如：otcol_traces、otcol_metrics、otcol_logs），你也可以在同一 sidecar 新建多个 pipeline。本文保持 仅 traces 简洁配置。

⸻

2) 可选方案：Spring Boot（3.x）Micrometer/OTel 原生埋点

当不能使用 Java Agent 时，可走 Micrometer Tracing + OpenTelemetry。此法通常需要加依赖，少量配置；大多数 Spring MVC、WebClient、RestTemplate 的入站/出站会自动提取/注入上下文。

2.1 依赖（Maven）

<dependencies>
  <!-- Micrometer Tracing 桥接到 OpenTelemetry -->
  <dependency>
    <groupId>io.micrometer</groupId>
    <artifactId>micrometer-tracing-bridge-otel</artifactId>
  </dependency>

  <!-- OTLP 导出器 -->
  <dependency>
    <groupId>io.opentelemetry</groupId>
    <artifactId>opentelemetry-exporter-otlp</artifactId>
  </dependency>

  <!-- 可选：日志相关桥接（将 traceId/spanId 注入日志 MDC） -->
  <dependency>
    <groupId>io.micrometer</groupId>
    <artifactId>micrometer-tracing</artifactId>
  </dependency>
</dependencies>

Gradle 同理添加。

2.2 配置（application.yml）

Spring Boot 3.1+ 常用如下属性（不同小版本命名略有差异，以下为通用写法；也可用 OTEL_* 环境变量）

management:
  tracing:
    enabled: true
    sampling:
      probability: 1.0           # 联调期全采样
  otlp:
    tracing:
      # 指向本 Pod 的 sidecar（OTLP HTTP）
      endpoint: http://127.0.0.1:4318/v1/traces

# 明确服务名（也可用 OTEL_SERVICE_NAME 环境变量）
spring:
  application:
    name: api1

若你使用 RestTemplate 手写 Bean，确保其被 RestTemplateBuilder 或 Micrometer 拦截器包装；使用 WebClient 通常自动处理。
如需兼容 Reactor/WebFlux、Feign、OkHttp 等，建议改用 Java Agent，自动覆盖面更广。

⸻

3) 关键点与易错项
	1.	上下文提取/注入
	•	Java Agent：自动对 Servlet/MVC、WebFlux、RestTemplate、WebClient 等做提取/注入。
	•	Micrometer：大多数场景能自动，但自定义 HTTP Client/线程池/异步任务需要手动把 Context 传递或使用框架的装饰器。
	2.	采样一致
	•	推荐 ParentBased(TraceIdRatio)，Kong 与 API 统一策略。联调 100% 采样，稳定后下调，例如 0.05。
	3.	W3C 传播器
	•	与 Kong 保持 tracecontext,baggage，必要时额外开启 b3 兼容旧链路：OTEL_PROPAGATORS=tracecontext,baggage,b3.
	4.	K8s 元数据
	•	使用 k8sattributes processor，方便在后端按命名空间/Pod/Deployment 过滤分析。
	5.	端口可达性
	•	App→Sidecar 使用 127.0.0.1:4318/4317，不受 NetworkPolicy 影响。
	•	Sidecar→Kafka 请确认命名空间/防火墙放通。
	6.	版本与协议
	•	统一 OTLP/HTTP（4318）或 OTLP/gRPC（4317），前后端一致；本文示例为 HTTP。
	7.	Kong 与 API 的出口分流
	•	Kong：发到集中式 Collector或 Kong 自身 sidecar。
	•	API：发到各自 Pod 的 sidecar。最终都进入 Kafka（可同一 topic）。

⸻

4) 联调与验证

4.1 快速自检（API Pod 内）
	•	查看 sidecar 日志：应看到 OTLP 接收与 Kafka 导出成功日志（无 export failed）。
	•	将 OTEL_TRACES_SAMPLER_ARG=1.0，确保全量采样便于观察。

4.2 端到端验证步骤
	1.	仅开启 API1 的 Java Agent 和 sidecar，curl 调用 API1，看是否能在后端（Kafka 消费者/Tempo UI）看到以 service.name=api1 的 Span。
	2.	开启 API2/3 同样配置，让 API1 调 API2、API2 调 API3。
	3.	从 Kong 入流量，确认在 UI 里能看到：kong（入口）→api1→api2→api3 的连续 Span（同一 trace_id）。

若出现断链：
	•	检查响应/出站是否注入了 traceparent；
	•	是否有自定义反向代理/安全组件剥离头部；
	•	采样是否父不采样子采样；
	•	时间同步是否异常导致 Span 顺序错乱。

⸻

5) Mermaid：数据/上下文流示意

flowchart LR
    subgraph Pod_API1
      A1[App (Spring Boot: api1)]
      C1[OTel Collector Sidecar]
    end
    subgraph Pod_API2
      A2[App (api2)]
      C2[Collector Sidecar]
    end
    subgraph Pod_API3
      A3[App (api3)]
      C3[Collector Sidecar]
    end
    subgraph Kafka
      K[(otcol_traces topic)]
    end

    Client-->KongDP
    KongDP-- tracecontext/baggage -->A1
    A1-- inject ctx -->A2
    A2-- inject ctx -->A3

    A1-- OTLP -->C1--->K
    A2-- OTLP -->C2--->K
    A3-- OTLP -->C3--->K


⸻

6) 你可以直接复用的「差异点清单」
	•	API2/3：复制 API1 的 Deployment/ConfigMap，改：
	•	name/labels → api2 / api3
	•	OTEL_SERVICE_NAME → api2 / api3
	•	ConfigMap 名 → api2-otelcol-config / api3-otelcol-config
	•	Kafka：把 brokers 与安全参数替换成你的实际值；如你已有 otcol_traces 规范，保持一致即可。
	•	采样率：压测/联调阶段用 1.0，生产期根据成本与 SLO 逐步下调。

⸻

需要我把 API2/3 的 YAML 也按上面的模板完整生成出来，或根据你现有命名空间/镜像名/Kafka 安全参数替换成可直接 kubectl apply 的版本吗？

send-mail: improve checks for valid_fqdn

The current implementation of a valid Fully Qualified Domain Name
is not that strict. It just checks whether it has a dot (.) and
if using macOS, it should not end with .local. As per RFC1035[1],
from what I understood, the following checks need to be done:

- The domain must contain atleast one dot
- Each label (separated by dots) must be 1-63 characters long
- Labels must start and end with an alphanumeric character
- Labels can contain alphanumeric characters and hyphens

Here are some examples of valid and invalid labels:

'example.com',          # Valid
'sub.example.com',      # Valid
'my-domain.org',        # Valid
'localhost',            # Invalid (no dot)
'MacBook..',            # Invalid (double dots)
'-example.com',         # Invalid (starts with a hyphen)
'example-.com',         # Invalid (ends with a hyphen)
'example..com',         # Invalid (double dots)
'example',              # Invalid (no TLD)
'example.local',        # Invalid on macOS
'valid-domain.co.uk',   # Valid
'123.example.com',      # Valid
'example.com.',         # Invalid (trailing dot)
'toolonglabeltoolonglabeltoolonglabeltoolonglabeltoolonglabeltoolonglabel.com', # Invalid (label > 63 chars)

Due to current implementation, I was not able to send emails from
Ubuntu. Upon debugging, I found that the SMTP domain being passed
to Outlook's servers was not valid.

Net::SMTP=GLOB(0x5db4351225f8)>>> EHLO MacBook..
Net::SMTP=GLOB(0x5db4351225f8)<<< 501 5.5.4 Invalid domain name
Net::SMTP=GLOB(0x5db4351225f8)>>> HELO MacBook..

Notice that an invalid domain name "MacBook.." is sent by git-send-email.
We have a fallback code that checks output from Net::Domain::domainname()
or asking domain method of an Net::SMTP instance to detect a misconfigured
hostname and replace it with fallback "localhost.localdomain", but the
valid_fqdn apparently is failing to say "MacBook.." is not a valid fqdn.

With this patch, the rule used in valid_fqdn is tightened, the beginning
part of the SMTP exchange looked like this:

Net::SMTP=GLOB(0x58c8af71e930)>>> EHLO localhost.localdomain
Net::SMTP=GLOB(0x58c8af71e930)<<< 250-PN4P287CA0064.outlook.office365.com Hello

[1]: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc1035

sequencer: rework reflog message handling

It has been reported that "git rebase --rebase-merges" can create
corrupted reflog entries like

    e9c962f2ea0 HEAD@{8}: <binary>�: Merged in <branch> (pull request #4441)

This is due to a use-after-free bug that happens because
reflog_message() uses a static `struct strbuf` and is not called to
update the current reflog message stored in `ctx->reflog_message` when
creating the merge. This means `ctx->reflog_message` points to a stale
reflog message that has been freed by subsequent call to
reflog_message() by a command such as `reset` that used the return value
directly rather than storing the result in `ctx->reflog_message`.

Fix this by creating the reflog message nearer to where the commit is
created and storing it in a local variable which is passed as an
additional parameter to run_git_commit() rather than storing the message
in `struct replay_ctx`. This makes it harder to forget to call
`reflog_message()` before creating a commit and using a variable with a
narrower scope means that a stale value cannot carried across a from one
iteration of the loop to the next which should prevent any similar
use-after-free bugs in the future.

A existing test is modified to demonstrate that merges are now created
with the correct reflog message.

Signed-off-by: Phillip Wood <phillip.wood@dunelm.org.uk>
Signed-off-by: Junio C Hamano <gitster@pobox.com>

Makefile: avoid constant rebuilds with compilation database

Many contributors to software use a Language Server Protocol
implementation to allow their editor to learn structural information
about the code they write and provide additional features, such as
jumping to the declaration or definition of a function or type.  In C,
the usual implementation is clangd, which requires compiling with clang.

Because C and C++ projects lack a standard file system layout and build
system, unlike languages such as Rust and Go, clangd requires a
compilation database to be generated by the clang compiler in order to
pass the proper compilation flags and discover all of the files
necessary to make the LSP work.  This is done by setting
GENERATE_COMPILATION_DATABASE to "yes".

However, when that's enabled and the user runs "make" a second time,
all of the files are re-compiled, which is inconvenient for contributors
to Git, since it makes small changes or rebases recompile the entirety
of the codebase.  This happens because the directory holding the
compilation database is updated anytime an object is built, so its
modification date will always be newer than the first object built.

To solve this, use the same trick we do just above for the .depend
directory and filter the compilation database directory out if it
already exists, which avoids making it a target to be built.

![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

This `useEffect` introduces a race condition that can cause the user's chat history to be erased on page load. Here's the sequence:
1. On initial render, `messages` is an empty array `[]`.
2. This effect runs and saves `[]` to `sessionStorage`, overwriting any existing history.
3. Subsequently, the `useEffect` at line 41 runs to load history from storage, but it might be too late.

This happens because `setMessages` in the loading effect is asynchronous and the effects from the initial render complete before the state is updated. A robust solution involves either making the initial state load synchronous (e.g., with `useState`'s lazy initializer) or using a `useRef` flag to prevent this effect from running on the very first render. Since those changes are outside the diff, I'd recommend revisiting the state initialization logic to prevent this bug.

issue.title: mpremote: enter_raw_repl: not working with micropython v1.26
issue.body:
### Port, board and/or hardware

esp32-s3, mpremote

### MicroPython version

micropython v1.26 with ESP32-S3

### Reproduction

mpremote cp process_handler.py :/process_handler.py 

### Expected behaviour

Should copy

### Observed behaviour

`mpremote.transport.TransportError: could not enter raw repl`


### Additional Information

I observed that from being in raw REPL, you cannot initiate a reboot with CTRL-D any more like it was in earlier micropython version.
For reboot, you now need to leave the raw REPL with CTRL-A first before being able to reboot with CTRL-D.

So the behavior of `enter_raw_repl` in `transport_serial.py`might need modification.

### Code of Conduct

Yes, I agree
